s/img/expansions/BR_logo2.png"><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/idoneth-deepkin/Eidolon-of-Mathlann-Aspect-of-the-Storm" style="color:#101010">Eidolon of Mathlann, Aspect of the Storm</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div></span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00026"><b><p>The LEVIADON keyword is used in following Idoneth Deepkin warscrolls:</p></b><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Behemoth</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><img class="tooltip logo2" title="Expansion. Broken Realms: Morathi (2th edition, version 1.0)" src="/aos/img/expansions/BR_logo2.png"><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/idoneth-deepkin/Akhelian-Leviadon" style="color:#101010">Akhelian Leviadon</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div></span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00027"><b><p>The <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#WIZARDS">WIZARD</a> keyword is used in following Idoneth Deepkin warscrolls:</p></b><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Leader</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/idoneth-deepkin/Isharann-Tidecaster" style="color:#101010">Isharann Tidecaster</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><img class="tooltip logo2" title="Expansion. Broken Realms: Morathi (2th edition, version 1.0)" src="/aos/img/expansions/BR_logo2.png"><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/idoneth-deepkin/Eidolon-of-Mathlann-Aspect-of-the-Sea" style="color:#101010">Eidolon of Mathlann, Aspect of the Sea</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div></span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00028"><b><p>The AKHELIAN keyword is used in following Idoneth Deepkin warscrolls:</p></b><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">None</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/idoneth-deepkin/Akhelian-Ishlaen-Guard" style="color:#101010">Akhelian Ishlaen Guard</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/idoneth-deepkin/Akhelian-Morrsarr-Guard" style="color:#101010">Akhelian Morrsarr Guard</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><img class="tooltip logo2" title="Expansion. Broken Realms: Morathi (2th edition, version 1.0)" src="/aos/img/expansions/BR_logo2.png"><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/idoneth-deepkin/Akhelian-Allopexes" style="color:#101010">Akhelian Allopexes</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Leader</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/idoneth-deepkin/Akhelian-King" style="color:#101010">Akhelian King</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/idoneth-deepkin/Volturnos-High-King-of-the-Deep" style="color:#101010">Volturnos, High King of the Deep</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Behemoth</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><img class="tooltip logo2" title="Expansion. Broken Realms: Morathi (2th edition, version 1.0)" src="/aos/img/expansions/BR_logo2.png"><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/idoneth-deepkin/Akhelian-Leviadon" style="color:#101010">Akhelian Leviadon</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div></span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00029"><b><p>The NAMARTI keyword is used in following Idoneth Deepkin warscrolls:</p></b><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">None</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/idoneth-deepkin/Namarti-Reavers" style="color:#101010">Namarti Reavers</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Battleline</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/idoneth-deepkin/Namarti-Thralls" style="color:#101010">Namarti Thralls</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div></span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00030"><b><p>The AKHELIAN GUARD keyword is used in following Idoneth Deepkin warscrolls:</p></b><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">None</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/idoneth-deepkin/Akhelian-Ishlaen-Guard" style="color:#101010">Akhelian Ishlaen Guard</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/idoneth-deepkin/Akhelian-Morrsarr-Guard" style="color:#101010">Akhelian Morrsarr Guard</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div></span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00031"><div class="tooltip_header">Piling In</div><a href="/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#Piling-In"><div class="tooltip_link"></div></a><div style="clear:both"></div>
A unit can make a pile-in move if it is within 3" of an enemy unit or has made a <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#CHARGE-PHASE">charge move</a> in the same turn. If this is the case, you can move each model in the unit up to 3". Each model must finish its pile-in move at least as close to the nearest enemy model as it was at the start of the move.
</span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00032"><div class="tooltip_header">Normal Moves</div><a href="/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#Normal-Moves"><div class="tooltip_link"></div></a><div style="clear:both"></div>
Moves made in the movement phase are referred to as normal moves, to differentiate them from charge moves (made in the <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#CHARGE-PHASE">charge phase</a>) and <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#Piling-In">pile-in</a> moves (made in the <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#COMBAT-PHASE">combat phase</a>). A model making a normal move can move a distance in inches equal to or less than the Move characteristic shown on its <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#WARSCROLLS-1">warscroll</a>.
</span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00033"><div class="tooltip_header">Roll-offs</div><a href="/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#Roll-offs"><div class="tooltip_link"></div></a><div style="clear:both"></div>
Sometimes a rule may require the players to make a roll-off. When this is the case, each of the players rolls a dice, and whoever rolls highest wins the roll-off. If there is a tie for the highest roll, make the roll-off again. Neither player is allowed to re-roll or modify any of the dice when making a roll-off.
